                "revisionId": 2792491,
                "section": "Acquisition",
                "excerpt": "This mod can be obtained at the penultimate mission of The Sacrifice , automatically ranked to level 5. Additional unranked mods can be bought from Cephalon Simaris for 100,000 Standing 100,000 ."
              }
            }
          ],
          "mechanicsEvidence": {
            "status": "draft",
            "notes": [
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Pressure",
                  "pageId": 1312690,
                  "revisionId": 2792491,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Sacrificial Pressure is essentially the Pressure Point mod with Legendary rarity and 5 more ranks. It is considered the same mod as its Common counterpart, and thus both mods cannot be equipped together. The same is true for Primed Pressure Point ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Pressure",
                  "pageId": 1312690,
                  "revisionId": 2792491,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The set bonus for Sacrificial Pressure increases all stats given by the mod by 25% of mod's value per set pieces. At max rank with full set bonus, Sacrificial Pressure grants a melee damage bonus of +137.5% and a Sentient damage bonus of +41.3% ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Pressure",
                  "pageId": 1312690,
                  "revisionId": 2792491,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "This mod only surpasses Pressure Point at rank 9 with both set mods but fails to surpass Primed Pressure Point even at rank 10."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Pressure",
                  "pageId": 1312690,
                  "revisionId": 2792491,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "However, the significant boost to Critical Chance from Sacrificial Steel putting it over double of True Steel can make up for this."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Pressure",
                  "pageId": 1312690,
                  "revisionId": 2792491,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Umbra mods have a unique Umbra polarity, whose matching polarity can currently only be found on Excalibur Umbra , Exalted Umbra Blade , and the Skiajati . It is possible to (re-)add an Umbra polarity to a mod slot but only through the use of Umbra Forma , which are unique rare rewards from Nightwave , so it is advised not to re-Forma any mod slot with an Umbra polarity."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Pressure",
                  "pageId": 1312690,
                  "revisionId": 2792491,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Similar to other Faction Damage Mods (i.e. Smite Grineer ), the bonus damage against Sentients gets applied on top of the base damage and any added elemental damage of the equipped melee weapon (see Damage for complete mechanics)."
                }
              }
